3GPP TS 29.520 V18.9.0; 5G System; Network Data Analytics Services.

NWDAF Roaming Analytics Subscriptions (Collection)

Create a new Individual NWDAF Roaming Analytics Subscription

Authorizations:
NoneoAuth2ClientCredentials
Request Body schema: application/json
required
required
Array of objects (EventSubscription) non-empty

Represents Roaming Analytics subscription for a specific event.

object (ReportingInformation)

Represents the type of reporting that the subscription requires.

notifUri
required
string (Uri)

String providing an URI formatted according to RFC 3986.

notifCorrId
required
string

Notification correlation identifier.

required
object (PlmnId)

When PlmnId needs to be converted to string (e.g. when used in maps as key), the string shall be composed of three digits "mcc" followed by "-" and two or three digits "mnc".

Array of objects (EventNotification) non-empty

Contains immediate reports for Roaming Analytics.

Array of objects (FailureEventInfo) non-empty

Contains information about failed events.

suppFeat
string (SupportedFeatures) ^[A-Fa-f0-9]*$

A string used to indicate the features supported by an API that is used as defined in clause 6.6 in 3GPP TS 29.500. The string shall contain a bitmask indicating supported features in hexadecimal representation Each character in the string shall take a value of "0" to "9", "a" to "f" or "A" to "F" and shall represent the support of 4 features as described in table 5.2.2-3. The most significant character representing the highest-numbered features shall appear first in the string, and the character representing features 1 to 4 shall appear last in the string. The list of features and their numbering (starting with 1) are defined separately for each API. If the string contains a lower number of characters than there are defined features for an API, all features that would be represented by characters that are not present in the string are not supported.

Responses

Callbacks

/{apiRoot}/nnwdaf-roaminganalytics/v1/subscriptions

Individual NWDAF Roaming Analytics Subscription resource (Document)

Update an existing Individual Roaming Analytics Subscription resource.

Authorizations:
NoneoAuth2ClientCredentials
path Parameters
subscriptionId
required
string

String identifying a subscription to the Nnwdaf_RoamingAnalytics service.

Request Body schema: application/json
required
required
Array of objects (EventSubscription) non-empty

Represents Roaming Analytics subscription for a specific event.

object (ReportingInformation)

Represents the type of reporting that the subscription requires.

notifUri
required
string (Uri)

String providing an URI formatted according to RFC 3986.

notifCorrId
required
string

Notification correlation identifier.

required
object (PlmnId)

When PlmnId needs to be converted to string (e.g. when used in maps as key), the string shall be composed of three digits "mcc" followed by "-" and two or three digits "mnc".

Array of objects (EventNotification) non-empty

Contains immediate reports for Roaming Analytics.

Array of objects (FailureEventInfo) non-empty

Contains information about failed events.

suppFeat
string (SupportedFeatures) ^[A-Fa-f0-9]*$

A string used to indicate the features supported by an API that is used as defined in clause 6.6 in 3GPP TS 29.500. The string shall contain a bitmask indicating supported features in hexadecimal representation Each character in the string shall take a value of "0" to "9", "a" to "f" or "A" to "F" and shall represent the support of 4 features as described in table 5.2.2-3. The most significant character representing the highest-numbered features shall appear first in the string, and the character representing features 1 to 4 shall appear last in the string. The list of features and their numbering (starting with 1) are defined separately for each API. If the string contains a lower number of characters than there are defined features for an API, all features that would be represented by characters that are not present in the string are not supported.

Responses

/{apiRoot}/nnwdaf-roaminganalytics/v1/subscriptions/{subscriptionId}
